programme.title: World's Greatest: Mountains
programme.desc: The earth’s fragile crust has folded and faulted, and nowhere are these natural forces more evident than in the world’s great mountains. Explore the highest peaks of the world’s terrain - the rugged realm between heaven and earth.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Global Cities
programme.desc: Travel to the centers of wealth, power, industry, and innovation. From London to Tokyo, Hong Kong to New York, these are the cities that never sleep. The influence held in these economic hubs unites the global community.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Capital Cities
programme.desc: With visionaries, politicians, and activists, these metropolises are defined as the official seats of government. Dublin, Washington, and Taipei share broad avenues, museums, and monuments, but are as varied as the countries they represent.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Ancient Cities
programme.desc: In Ancient Cities, we journey to these ancestors of influence such as Luang Prabang, Vienna, and Istanbul where religious and cultural centers have shaped the ways in which we view the world around us and continue to do so in modern times.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Wetland Animals
programme.desc: Wetland Animals dives into the swamps, rivers, and flood plains of the Everglades, Botswana’s Okavango Delta, Kakadu National Park in Australia, and the Amazon to see deadly crocodiles, piranhas, hippopotamus, flamingo, manatee, and platypus.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Nations
programme.desc: Though many are small in stature, they have punched well above their weight on the global stage. Some are rooted in ancient history, while others are only just beginning to realize their full potential.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Mega Cities
programme.desc: Mega Cities provide a bustling home to populations of over 10 million. Travel from the high-density living of Shanghai and Bangkok to the sprawling cities of Delhi and Mexico City, each the backdrop for dynamic cultures.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Jungle Animals
programme.desc: Encounter gorillas and orangutans, killer tree-dwelling pythons, delightful monkeys, awe-inspiring tigers, and millions of land-dwelling red crabs in Australia, the islands of Southeast Asia, Africa, and the Amazon.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Coral Islands
programme.desc: The reef systems that gave rise to coral islands support the vast majority of marine species on our planet, but they are under threat. Explore the delicate balance between exploiting and preserving these extraordinary natural wonders.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Lost Cities
programme.desc: Once powerful and populous centers of influence, these lost cities are providing clues to how our ancestors existed in the world and remind us that ancient civilizations were not so far removed from our own.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Forest Animals
programme.desc: Forest Animals gets up close with bears, koalas, moose, wolves, weaver ants, and Tasmanian Devils. This episode roves dark forests floors and soars above vast canopies of green in America, China, Laos, and Australia.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Flights
programme.desc: Our experience of the world’s greatest marvels is literally and figuratively elevated when we explore them from the air. Whether you travel by air balloon, helicopter, light aircraft, a grand perspective is always guaranteed.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Rivers
programme.desc: Rivers flow freely - beautiful and powerful waterways that underscore the melody of life. As they meander through the landscape, they shape it, wearing down ranges and deepening valleys, eventually flowing out into the sea.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Archipelagos
programme.desc: The romantic notion of island life has always attracted us. Explore the histories, cultures, and unique ways of life on the World’s Greatest Archipelagos - clusters of islands that share common bonds of geography, geology, and genealogy.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Cruises
programme.desc: There is something seductive about setting sail. Cruises offer us a chance to dip our toes into the 70% of our planet awash with oceans, rivers, and lakes, exploring places that can only be reached by daring to leave the shore.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Sacred Sites
programme.desc: Ancient in architecture and detailed in design, these man-made masterpieces stand as testaments to the strength of human faith. These sites endure as a timeless reminder of resilience, respect, and the need to reflect.

programme.title: World's Greatest: Island Arks
programme.desc: Cut off from continents, remote islands have become floating arks, attracting migrating species and forging new ones. Take a privileged glimpse into the secret lives of the rare and exotic species that inhabit these lost worlds.

programme.title: Battle of Britain: The Race For Radar
programme.desc: On the brink of war the Germans mount a daring Zeppelin spy mission. Had the Luftwaffe spies discovered Britain’s greatest secret?'

programme.title: Battlefront: WWII Road To Victory: U-Boat War
programme.desc: U-boats posed the deadliest threat to Allied convoys traveling the Atlantic.

programme.title: War Story: Where Hell is: The Leopold and the Scheldt
programme.desc: The Allies liberated Antwerp, the world’s largest deep-water port, on 4 September 1944, but it could only be accessed via the Scheldt Estuary, the perfect place for the Germans to make a stand.
programme.sub-title: Where Hell is: The Leopold and the Scheldt

programme.title: War Story: Falaise, the corridor of death
programme.desc: The Canadian army played the pivotal role in closing the Falaise Gap and ensuring Allied victory in the Normandy Campaign in August 1944.

programme.title: War Story: D-Day plus 1
programme.desc: The Canadian stand against the 12th SS Panzer Division Hitlerjugend immediately after D-Day allowed the Allies to switch to the offensive and truly begin the liberation of Europe.

programme.title: War Story: Surviving Dieppe
programme.desc: The Dieppe assault of 19 August 1942 is the worst day in Canadian military history: in just 8 hours, 907 Canadians were killed. For 2,000 of their comrades, nearly three years of incarceration in German prison camps followed.

programme.title: War Story: Whistle for a Tiffy
programme.desc: From D-Day, Tactical Air Force fighter-bombers played a pivotal role in Allied battlefield success; Canadian soldiers knew they could always “whistle for a Tiffy”.

programme.title: War Story: Behind Enemy Lines
programme.desc: Royal Canadian Air Force bombing operations play a crucial role in disrupting German infrastructure ahead of the Normandy invasion of June 1944. In the process, dozens of Canadian airmen are forced to bail out over occupied Belgium and France.

programme.title: War Story: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad
programme.desc: In the summer of 1942, the Germans advance to seize the rich oilfields of the Caucasus. In their path, the city of Stalingrad, its Soviet defenders personally ordered by Stalin to “take not one step back".
programme.sub-title: Not One Step Back: The Battle of Stalingrad

programme.title: War Story: Buchenwald Airmen
programme.desc: For two months in 1944, 168 Allied airmen were shot down over occupied France, betrayed to the Gestapo by the same collaborator, transported to the Nazi concentration and slave labour camp Buchenwald.

programme.title: War Story: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt
programme.desc: On 16 April 1945, a mere three weeks before German surrender, the submarine fired a single torpedo that sank the last Canadian naval vessel lost to enemy action.
programme.sub-title: The Last Ship: The Sinking of the Esquimalt

programme.title: War Story: Prisoners of the Sun
programme.desc: On 16 November 1941, two Canadian battalions arrived in the British colony of Hong Kong. Their aim: Bolster the Empire’s defenses in the event of aggression by the restless forces of Japan, stationed only kilometres away in occupied China.

programme.title: War Story: Vengeance
programme.desc: In 1941, nearly 30,000 Jews escaped the ghettos and work camps and they joined the growing underground resistance army, actively fighting the Nazis.

programme.title: War Story: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany
programme.desc: In mid-September 1944, the remnants of the battered 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion participated in the largest parachute drop in history, fought a successful battle.
programme.sub-title: Across the Rhine: Paras in Germany

programme.title: War Story: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy
programme.desc: In Normandy, the 1st Canadian Parachute Battalion proved itself to be in the vanguard of the best-trained and toughest units in the Allied forces.
programme.sub-title: Out of the Clouds: Paras in Normandy

programme.title: War Story: The Road to Rome
programme.desc: The Road to Rome examines the incredible experiences of Canadian veterans, the victories and horrors of armoured combat, and the pivotal value, far too often neglected, of the overall Italian Campaign.

programme.title: War Story: Ortona: The War Inside
programme.desc: The War Inside is a personal retelling of one of the fiercest battles of the Italian Campaign from the searing points of view of Canadian infantrymen, a tanker, a stretcher bearer, and a German paratrooper.

programme.title: War Story: Sicily: The First Campaign
programme.desc: The Sicily Campaign began with the largest seaborne invasion in history on 9-10 July 1943. The Allied forces of Britain, Canada, and the United States sought to knock Italy out of the war and attack Germany from the south.

programme.title: War Story: Bomb Girls Remember
programme.desc: During the Second World War, 250,000 Canadian women helped to build the arsenal of democracy. These young women met the challenges of factory work and helped to win the Second World War, and by doing so, paved the way for future generations.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Getting Home
programme.desc: In this film, Bomber Command personnel and a Luftwaffe pilot take the viewer through the frightening reality of fighting in the skies as they try to get a damaged bomber home.

programme.title: War Story: Bomber Command: Hitting Back
programme.desc: After surviving the German bombing campaign of British cities, RAF Bomber Command struck back against Germany. The devastating consequences of raids, for both for the young men in the skies and the people on the ground, are portrayed in this film.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Japan continues its suicidal resistance, and invading it looks costly. After 2 atomic bombs, the Emperor intervenes and stops the War. Stalin grabs territory in East Asia. The War is over, and the Atomic Era and the Cold War start.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: In 1945, Germany is crumbly on both fronts. The Western Allies cross the Rhine and take most of Germany, while the Red Army quickly advances into Berlin. After Hitler's suicide, Germany surrenders and is divided among the allied powers.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Marines succeed in the "island hopping" strategy against suicidal resistance. The US Navy establishes supremacy, cutting off Japan.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: The Western Allies secure supply routes that will allow them to enter Germany, and the Ardennes counter-offensive fails. The Red Army advances rapidly. The SS implements the Holocaust.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: After a careful campaign of disinformation that throws the German defenders off-guard, the Western Allies finally land on Normandy.France is liberated.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Their attack on the Soviet Union having failed, the German Army suffers a series of counter-offensives on the Eastern Front. Wehrmacht's losses are huge as the Soviets advance West.

programme.title: NEW: World War II in HD Colour
programme.desc: Allies turn the tide in the Atlantic, where initially German U-Boats harass freely convoys to supply Britain. The route to bring American soldiers who will land on D-Day is clear.

programme.title: Secret Nazi Expeditions: Runes
programme.desc: Runes are the letters of an ancient Germanic writing system that harkens back to a mythological age filled with heroes, magic, and mystery.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: X-Rated
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler had a depraved sex life that he tried to keep hidden from the German public. He was said to be a chronic masturbator, a voyeur and that he engaged in sado-masochistic sex with women.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Body Image
programme.desc: Hitler wanted the world to believe he possessed super-human qualities but in private he was a wreck. This episode reveals the archives that confirm Hitler’s genital deformity, the alarming truth about his heavy drug addiction and the Parkinson’s.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Family Matters
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler's father was a violent, abusive man. His mother doted on her young son. This episode delves deep into the psychology of Hitler as the narcissistic child who grew into a malignant psychopath full of rage and deep hatred.

programme.title: Hitler's Secret Sex Life: Suicidal Maidens
programme.desc: Using extensive archival research, this program explores the squalid secrets he lied and killed to protect

programme.title: Architects Of Darkness: Adolf Hitler
programme.desc: Adolf Hitler: The film explores the roots of Adolf Hitler and traces the story of his life from the town of his birth to his final days.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.
programme.desc: From the Protection Squadron to the SS State: Trace the rise to power of the SS as we examine several perpetrators. Who was recruited? And why was the SS attractive to men?
programme.sub-title: From The "Protection Squadron" To The SS State.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Heinrich Himmler
programme.desc: Heinrich Himmler: An agriculturalist by trade, he went on to lead the SS and tried to escape responsibility at the end of the war. Who was Heinrich Himmler?

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich
programme.desc: The Executioner: Reinhard Heydrich: More than any other Nazi leader, Heydrich was an orchestrator of mass murder, and was terrifyingly clinical in approach.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The Waffen-SS
programme.desc: The Waffen-SS: Masqueraded as military excellence, the reality was very different. Recruits were poorly trained and remorse was nonexistent, as SS troops killed mercilessly.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: The SS Death Head's Unit
programme.desc: The SS Death Head's Unit: Tasked with guarding concentration camps, this unit's actions knew no bounds, and, despite their heinous acts, still attended social gatherings.

programme.title: Beyond The Myth: The SS Unveiled: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945
programme.desc: Unrepentant: The SS and Its Myth After 1945: Drawing a line to the present, the atrocities of the SS are beyond all doubt, yet, there is a cult surrounding 'old comrades' today.
programme.sub-title: Unrepentant: The SS And Its Myth After 1945

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922
programme.desc: The Seeds of Violence 1918-1922: In the wake of the First World War, Adolf Hitler identifies Benito Mussolini as his model and has one ultimate goal: to gain power in Germany.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928
programme.desc: Deceit and Delusion 1923-1928: Hitler appears to be eliminated after his failed putsch in 1923. Discover how the Nazi movement used democracy's tolerance in Germany to come back.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Democracy without Democrats 1929-1933
programme.desc: Democracy Without Democrats 1929-1933: A protest turns into a racist and anti-Jewish movement during the 1920s and the NSDAP use emotions to gain the loyalty of the people.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Racial State 1933-1934
programme.desc: The Racial State 1933-1934: President Hindenburg suspends freedom of speech and Hitler comes to power in 1933. The first concentration camps for political opponents are set up.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Hidden in Plain Sight 1935-1938
programme.desc: Hidden In Plain Sight 1935-1938: In 1934, Hitler's government is firmly in the saddle. Most Germans support Hitler's anti-Jewish policy and the regime's terror soon escalates.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Up in Flames 1936-1940
programme.desc: Up in Flames 1936-1940: At the end of 1939, the German Army invades Poland. Examine how Hitler succeeded in pushing through his rearmament and war plans relatively unhindered.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942
programme.desc: The Gates of Hell 1941-1942: In the shadow of the war, the Nazi regime gradually advances its "final solution to the Jewish problem", culminating in the Holocaust.

programme.title: The Abyss: Rise And Fall of The Nazis: Genocide 1942-1944
programme.desc: Genocide 1942 - 1944: Along with Treblinka and Majdanek, Sobibor was one of the camps used in Operation Reinhard, in which the Nazis murdered almost two million people.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls
programme.desc: Marooned for ten days, the islanders now face starvation. They battle dangerous ocean currents to set fishing nets. Rob develops a tooth abscess, and endures primitive surgery on the beach. And flickers of romance begin.

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: The Island with Bear Grylls

programme.title: Survivorman

programme.title: Survivorman

programme.title: Survivorman

programme.desc: The first big mistake Ralph makes is not clearing the snow from the front walk, and his life goes downhill from that point on. By the end of the story, the mailman has fatally slipped on his job, and Alice, his wife, doesn't live there anymore.

programme.title: Goddess Remembered
programme.desc: This poetic documentary is a salute to 35 000 years of "pre-history," to the values of ancestors only recently remembered, and to the goddess-worshipping religions of the ancient past.

programme.title: Hands Of History
programme.desc: In this acclaimed 1994 documentary, Loretta Todd, a leading figure in Indigenous cinema in Canada, profiles four contemporary female artists.The film is a moving testimony to the vital role Indigenous women play in nurturing Indigenous cultures.

programme.title: Sea Dream
programme.desc: Children, like adults, have days that go wrong. This film shows how one little girl overcomes the day's frustrations by diving into an underwater fantasy where she spends time with her friend, the lady octopus.

programme.title: How They Saw Us Women At Work
programme.desc: This is an abridged version of a film made in 1958. The greater part of the film accepts as normal the waste of women's talents in repetitive or service jobs, while elevating this work to the status of a career.

programme.title: Neighbours Voisins
programme.desc: Two neighbours live side by side in harmony until a flower grows on the dividing line between their properties. Who does it belong to? The argument that follows ends up with both neighbours in their graves. The most famous of Norman McLaren’s films.

programme.title: Nobody Waved Good-Bye
programme.desc: A story of teenage conflict--the predicament of a youth who rebels against his parents' middle-class goals and conventions but finds the world, away from home and high school, a cold place to go it alone.

programme.title: King Of The Hill
programme.desc: Spring 1972. The Chicago Cubs are poised to win the National League's Pennant race, lead by their star pitcher, a Black Canadian named Ferguson Jenkins, who was inducted into the Baseball Hall of Fame in 1991. This is his story.

programme.title: Sun Wind And Wood
programme.desc: People combat high energy costs with inventive solar, wind, and wood solutions. This film showcases experiments like the Ark, a bio-shelter sustaining a family with housing, heat, food, and electricity using natural systems.

programme.title: Mother Earth/La Terre Notre Mere
programme.desc: Mother Earth is a short, evocative, poetic film that celebrates life on our planet. This documentary film looks at the reality of human beings; the earth is our home and we are profoundly connected to all other beings.

programme.title: Tu As Crie Let Me Go
programme.desc: In "Tu as crié LET ME GO," Anne Claire Poirier explores her daughter's tragic descent into drugs and prostitution, seeking understanding of the societal pressures influencing young people's risky behaviors in Montreal's streets.

programme.title: Benoit
programme.desc: Benoît is an astonishingly accomplished eleven-year-old Québécois from Joliette. He pursues such diverse activities as weight lifting and playing the violin.

programme.title: Physics Of Sorrow, The
programme.desc: The Physics of Sorrow tracks an unknown man’s life as he sifts through memories of his youth in Bulgaria through to his increasingly rootless and melancholic adulthood in Canada.

programme.title: Beyond Paper
programme.desc: In the era of the digital revolution, the transmission of knowledge is going through a profound upheaval as humanity’s archives migrate from paper to the cloud. How can we grasp the impact of the ongoing abandonment of books on thought and learning?

programme.title: Mountain Of Sgaana
programme.desc: This film spins a magical tale of a young man who is stolen away to the spirit world, and the young woman who rescues him. Haida filmmaker Christopher Auchter’s dream-like gem brilliantly entwines traditional animation with formal elements of Haida art.

programme.title: Waiting
programme.desc: The patient Dinkas of South Sudan endure famine amid civil strife. Aid arrives in Alek, but distribution is delayed to prevent unrest, revealing the stark reality of hunger.

programme.title: Out Of Mind Out Of Sight
programme.desc: follows treatment processes at Brockville Mental Health Centre normally hidden from the public, profiling four patients as they struggle to gain control over their lives, so they can return to a society that often fears and demonizes them.

programme.title: If You Love This Planet
programme.desc: This film records a lecture given to students by outspoken nuclear critic, Dr. Helen Caldicott, president of Physicians for Social Responsibility in the United States. Her message is clear: disarmament cannot be postponed.

programme.title: Eine Hochzeit an Weihnachten
programme.desc: Haley Foster entkam ihrer Kleinstadt-Kindheit in Pineridge und baute sich ein Großstadtleben in Los Angeles als Top-Hochzeitsplanerin in einer elitären und mächtigen Firma auf, die von Frau Reynolds geleitet wird.

programme.title: Weihnachten in Alaska
programme.desc: Als die Geschäftsfrau Jennifer erfährt, dass ihre Eltern in den Ferien ohne sie unterwegs sein werden, beschließt sie, ihr geschäftiges Stadtleben in San Francisco zu verlassen, um das Gasthaus ihrer Großmutter zu besuchen.

programme.title: Der Weihnachts-Song
programme.desc: Budgetkürzungen zwingen zwei New Yorker Hochschulen zu fusionieren. Ein Musiklehrer und eine Lehrerin konkurrieren im größten Weihnachts-Song Wettbewerb des Landes um die Arbeitsstelle des...

programme.title: Christmas Land
programme.desc: Christmas Land hat seit dem tragischen Tod von Glinda schon bessere Tage gesehen, und Jules muss viele komplizierte Entscheidungen treffen.

programme.title: Die Weihnachtstruppe
programme.desc: Die arbeitslose Kunstlehrerin Allie möchte Witwer Gordon und seine Töchter wieder für Weihnachten begeistern.

programme.title: Der magische Weihnachtsschmuck
programme.desc: Seit sie an Weihnachten sitzen gelassen wurde, hat Marie (Jessica Lowndes) mit dem Fest der Liebe abgeschlossen. Daran kann auch der Festtagsschmuck nichts ändern, den ihre Mutter ihr täglich zukommen lässt.

programme.title: Ein perfektes Weihnachten
programme.desc: Holly Maddux fehlt zu ihrem Glück nur noch der perfekte Mann. Nach einem Sturz vor dem Geschäft schwebt Holly im siebten Himmel, denn ihr Traummann steht plötzlich vor ihr...

programme.title: Weihnachten in den Highlands
programme.desc: Dieses Weihnachten wird Blair Henderson, eine Parfümexpertin aus New York, von ihrer Chefin ins ferne Schottland geschickt, um einen seltenen Duft zu finden.

programme.title: Die 12 Weihnachtsgeschenke

programme.title: Tempo de Natal

programme.title: Véspera de Natal
programme.desc: É véspera de Natal e um apagão vai obrigar alguns nova-iorquinos ocupados a ficarem presos dentro de elevadores enquanto esperam por ajuda. Essa longa noite juntos irá mudar suas vidas para sempre.

programme.title: O Projeto de Natal

programme.title: Dançando No Natal
programme.desc: Olívia, professora de ballet, escolhe a talentosa Lily como protagonista do espetáculo de Natal "O Quebra-Nozes" e acaba se apaixonando pelo pai dela, Michael, um bombeiro atraente. Com a ajuda dele, Olívia tentará salvar seu estúdio de dança.

programme.title: Bailey, Um Herói do Natal
programme.desc: É "época de Natal" e Bailey, preocupado em não receber presentes por ter sido um cachorro mau, descobre sobre um misterioso índio americano nativo que pode ser capaz de realizar seus desejos.

programme.title: Uma Aventura de Natal
programme.desc: O Natal na casa dos Nolan não é o que costumava ser. Em uma viagem de compras de última hora com papai, a família entra em uma loja encantada apenas para descobrir um globo de neve deslumbrante com poderes mágicos.

programme.title: 12 Dias De Presentes
programme.desc: Um homem ganha uma fortuna e decide compartilhar o prêmio com as pessoas de sua pequena cidade, mas ele não podia imaginar que o amor seria uma de suas recompensas.

programme.title: O Natal de Caillou, o filme
programme.desc: É inverno na casa de Caillou, e o curioso menino de quatro anos recebe a estação com a sua curiosidade e entusiasmo de sempre.

programme.title: Querido Papai Noel Secreto
programme.desc: Jennifer começa a trocar cartas com um admirador secreto de seu passado. Agora que ela tem uma segunda chance no amor, ela será capaz de aproveitá-la?

programme.title: 12 Presentes de Natal
programme.desc: Quando Anna, uma pintora desempregada, é incapaz de sobreviver, ela é contratada para se tornar uma compradora pessoal de Natal para Marc, um executivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Músicas de Natal
programme.desc: Crie uma atmosfera calorosa de férias em sua casa com as imagens e sons do Natal, filmados em alta definição.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Juntos esta Navidad
programme.desc: Luego de una ruptura amorosa, Isabel y el viudo Juan Andrés con su hija comparten, accidentalmente, una cabaña navideña. Circunstancias inusuales y la magia de las fiestas resultarán en una unión muy especial.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: Noche Serena: Entre el Coraje y la Fe
programme.desc: 1818 Austria, el sacerdote José, se enfrenta a una crisis antes de una elección crucial de Navidad.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Juntos esta Navidad
programme.desc: Luego de una ruptura amorosa, Isabel y el viudo Juan Andrés con su hija comparten, accidentalmente, una cabaña navideña. Circunstancias inusuales y la magia de las fiestas resultarán en una unión muy especial.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: Noche Serena: Entre el Coraje y la Fe
programme.desc: 1818 Austria, el sacerdote José, se enfrenta a una crisis antes de una elección crucial de Navidad.

programme.title: Un Pedido de Navidad
programme.desc: Una joven, del último año del secundario descubre que no podrá participar del baile anual de su ciudad porque tendrá que trabajar en el evento que la iglesia promueve la noche de navidad. Ella pide un deseo que se vuelve realidad.

programme.title: So this is Christmas
programme.desc: A los 18 años, Ashley sale con gente mala, y busca una fuga de la rutina de casa. Pero todo empieza a cambiar cuando uno de los empleados de la familia consigue animarla a hacer una pieza de teatro de Navidad para niños necesitados.

programme.title: Juntos esta Navidad
programme.desc: Luego de una ruptura amorosa, Isabel y el viudo Juan Andrés con su hija comparten, accidentalmente, una cabaña navideña. Circunstancias inusuales y la magia de las fiestas resultarán en una unión muy especial.

programme.title: 12 Regalos de navidad
programme.desc: Cuando Anna, una pintora desempleada, no puede llegar a fin de mes, la contratan para convertirse en la compradora navideña personal de Marc, un ejecutivo corporativo tenso.

programme.title: Una Navidad muy Britanica
programme.desc: El vuelo de la cantante de ópera Jessica a su concierto en Viena se retrasa y ella se queda varada en Yorkshire. El único lugar para quedarse es un bed and breakfast en un pueblo encantador dirigido por un apuesto viudo llamado Andrew.

programme.title: Una Navidad de Cuento
programme.desc: En esta alegre versión del clásico de Dickens, Carol (Tori Spelling) interpreta a una presentadora de programas de televisión egoísta que está decidida a destruir la diversión festiva en el estudio. Por sus acciones, tres espíritus la visitarán.

programme.title: It's a Christmas Thing
programme.desc: Cuando Megan, de nueve años, dedica su deseo navideño a ayudar a su madre Cara a encontrar el amor, su carta termina volviéndose viral. ¿Cara seguirá el consejo de su hija y encontrará el amor?

programme.title: Spotlight on Christmas
programme.desc: Abandonada dos semanas antes de Navidad, la actriz de Hollywood Olivia O'Hara regresa en secreto a su pequeña ciudad natal para evitar a la prensa. Cuando se topa con el profesor de secundaria Casey, él la anima a dirigir la obra navideña de su escuela.

programme.title: Christmas Chalet, The
programme.desc: Una amante de la Navidad y divorciada reserva un viaje a un chalet con su madre y su hija. Sin embargo, el mismo chalet está reservado para un único escritor que odia la Navidad. Juntos aprenden la magia de la Navidad y la familia.

programme.title: Noche Serena: Entre el Coraje y la Fe
programme.desc: 1818 Austria, el sacerdote José, se enfrenta a una crisis antes de una elección crucial de Navidad.

programme.desc: Wer heitere Partystimmung im heimischen Wohnzimmer haben will, ist bei der „Tanzparty“ auf GoldStar TV genau richtig. Heiße Rhythmen und Melodien mit schwungvoller Tanzmusik sorgen für eine perfekte Atmosphäre.

programme.title: GoldStar Hitcocktail II
programme.desc: Die Mischung macht's - Top-Hits aus aller Welt vereint in einem Hitcocktail!

programme.title: Die Flippers
programme.desc: Die Flippers machen sich auf in die Schweiz und dort in den malerischen Kanton Tessin. Wie kein anderer Landstrich vereint er einen Hauch "Bella Italia" mit der eindrucksvollen Landschaft der Alpen. Kein Wunder, dass er eines der beliebtesten Ferienziele in Europa ist. Mit im Gepäck hat das Hittrio Klassiker wie "Lass uns heute romantisch sein", "Der alte Maurice" und natürlich "Lago Maggiore".

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: Uwe Hübner hat die Münchener Freiheit zu Gast im GoldStar-TV-Studio. Besonders ausführlich spricht er mit den Gründungsmitgliedern Stefan Zauner und Aron Strobel, die Einges über die Erfolgsgeschichte und die größten Hits der Band zu erzählen haben.

programme.title: Peter Kraus LIVE
programme.desc: Sein Hüftschwung ist so legendär wie der von Elvis. Und als Sänger, Gitarrist und Gelegenheitsschauspieler war Peter Kraus einer der ersten deutschsprachigen Künstler, die den Rock'n'Roll im Nachkriegsdeutschland salonfähig machten - mit Songs wie 'Susi Rock', 'Sugar Baby' oder 'Schwarze Rose Rosemarie'.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute zu Gast in Bad Waltersdorf
programme.desc: Inmitten des oststeirischen Hügellandes, genauer gesagt in der Thermenregion Bad Waltersdorf, heißt Dagmar Obernosterer ihre Gäste willkommen. Diese Sendung steht ganz im Zeichen von heißen Quellen, romantischen Herbstlandschaften und hochkarätigen Stars. Mit dabei sind auch die Lokalmatadore aus der Steiermark, die Stoakogler. 1968 begann die Gruppe ihre musikalische Laufbahn und nach 43 Jahren Bühne haben sie 2011 ihre Karriere beendet. Sie präsentieren ein Medley ihrer erfolgreichsten Hits.

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: 1982 fing alles an: Nicole gewann mit dem Titel "Ein bisschen Frieden" den Grand Prix Eurovision de la Chanson in Harrogate/England. Über Nacht ist sie ein Star und das mit gerade mal 18 Jahren! "Bei Hübner“ spricht die erfolgreiche Sängerin ganz privat über Meilensteine ihrer Karriere, ihre große Liebe, ihre geheimen Ängste, Hoffnungen und Träume.

programme.title: Bei Hübner
programme.desc: Er war der „Junge mit der Mundharmonika“, denn gleich sein erster, war auch sein größter Hit: Bernd Clüver. GoldStar TV erinnert an den beliebten Sänger, der 2011 bei einem Treppensturz in seiner Wahlheimat Mallorca ums Leben kam. "Bei Hübner" spricht Bernd Clüver nicht nur über sein Leben auf der Bühne, sondern auch über Privates

programme.title: Wildes Portugal: Von der Küste bis zu den Inseln
programme.desc: Der Reichtum von Portugals Küstengewässern ist erstaunlich. Tausende von Kreaturen leben am Atlantischen Ozean im Wasser und zu Land. Und die Inselwelt der Azoren mitten im Atlantik ist eines der reichsten Ökosysteme der Welt.

programme.title: Wildes Indonesien
programme.desc: Dieser Film erforscht die Inselwelt Indonesiens - ein Paradies von Riesenpflanzen und Korallengärten mit Drachen, Tigern und Riesenaffen, ein Zentrum biologischer Vielfalt, ein Land von Vulkanen und eine der letzten wilden Regionen.

programme.title: Kanadas Küstenwölfe
programme.desc: Der Great Bear Regenwald an der Westküste Kanadas ist die Heimat der Küstenwölfe. Sie haben felsige Riffe, bewaldete Inseln und die tobende Pazifikküste zu ihrer Heimat gemacht. Das besondere an ihnen ist, dass sie nicht nur an Land jagen, sondern auch im Ozean. Die Dokumentation begleitet Naturführer Cal Humchitt und sein Team auf den Spuren der Küstenwölfe.

programme.title: Naturparadiese in Lateinamerika: Die Anden
programme.desc: Diese Serie feiert Lateinamerikas dramatischste Regionen, von den Hohen Anden zum dampfenden Amazonas, von den windigen Steppen Patagoniens zu den Sümpfen Venezuelas – atemberaubende Schönheit und eine aufregende, vielfältige Tierwelt.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Wir stehen alle auf irgendjemandes Speiseplan. Deshalb hat sich die in der Natur ausgebildete Spezialisierung auf eine bestimmte Beute und Nahrung auf so faszinierende Art weiterentwickelt. Fressen, ähnlich wie Sex, bereitet allen Tieren Freude, wenngleich in geringerer Intensivität.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Die Stille der Natur ist nur Fassade. Das Leben ist bestimmt von Anstrengungen und Kämpfen, großen und kleinen, die zu Sieg oder Niederlage führen. Diese Kämpfe betreffen alle und alles: Kämpfe um Essen, um Reviere und um Liebe.

programme.desc: Das Verschwinden von drei Männern in Russland wird für Jeremy Wade zu einem rätselhaften Fall.

programme.desc: Die Jagd nach einem 6 Meter großen Seemonster, das Menschen in der kanadischen Wildnis angreift.

programme.desc: Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf die Suche nach dem grausamen und fleischfressenden Tigerfisch.

programme.desc: Die Legende besagt, dass in den Tiefen des Amazonas ein großer böser Fisch lebt.

programme.desc: Jeremy Wade begibt sich in den Dschungel von Südamerika, um einen gefährlichen Fisch aufzuspüren.

programme.title: Der südostasiatische Süßwasserkugelfisch
programme.desc: Jeremy Wade begibt sich auf der Suche nach einem putzigen Killerfisch an den Mekong in Südostasien.

programme.title: Sardiniens wertvolle Muschelseide
programme.desc: Planet Wetlweit: Jedes Frühjahr findet auf Sardinien eine Prozession zu Ehren des Heiligen Antiochus statt. Die Einwohner legen Kostüme an, in den Kirchen werden Altartücher ausgelegt, die noch mit Muschelseide verziert sind - jenen Fasern, die die Fischer seit Jahrhunderten dem Meer entnahmen. Inzwischen sind diese Muscheln streng geschützt

programme.title: Cordóba, die Stadt der Patios
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Der ganze Stolz von Córdoba sind die Patios der Stadt - begrünte Innenhöfe, deren Wurzeln bis in die römische Antike und die Zeit der maurischen Herrschaft in Andalusien zurückreichen. Einmal im Jahr findet ein traditioneller Wettbewerb statt. Dann dreht sich alles um die Frage: Wer hat den schönsten Patio der ganzen Stadt?

programme.title: Kourou: Palmen, Raketen, Gefängnisinseln
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Lange war Französisch-Guayana an der Küste Südamerikas ein Schreckensort für Gefangene. Die Zuchthäuser dort galten als die härtesten Frankreichs. Heute sind von ihnen nur noch Ruinen übrig, die restauriert werden. Frankreich beginnt, dieses dunkle Kapitel seiner Geschichte aufzuarbeiten, nur einige Kilometer entfernt vom Weltraumbahnhof Kourou.

programme.title: Die Minenratten von Tansania
programme.desc: Im Forschungszentrum der Organisation APOPO in Tansania herrscht helle Aufregung: Eine Rattenmutter hat Junge geworfen - ein Riesenerfolg bei in Gefangenschaft lebenden Riesenhamsterratten. Schnell zeigt sich, dass einer der Rattenjungen besonders aufgeweckt ist. Er bekommt den Namen Ronaldinho. In nur wenigen Wochen lernt das intelligente Tier gefährliches TNT zu erschnüffeln.

programme.title: Montenegro
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Noch vor wenigen Jahren waren Esel in Montenegro vom Aussterben bedroht. Dass es die treuen Helfer noch immer gibt, ist vor allem Darko Savelji¿ zu verdanken. 2015 rettete der Biologe die erste, in elenden Verhältnissen gehaltene Eselstute. Kurze Zeit später nahm er zwei andere Esel zu sich, die als Futter für Jagdhunde geschlachtet werden sollten.

programme.title: Zuflucht in den Anden
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Am Tag arbeiten sie hart wie Männer. Am Abend verwandeln sie sich in das, als was sie sich fühlen: in Frauen. In ihren Gemeinden wurden sie verachtet und verstoßen. Auf den Kaffeeplantagen der kolumbianischen Anden, haben sie ein Refugium gefunden. Die Gemeinschaft von Transfrauen muss bis heute um ihre Anerkennung kämpfen

programme.title: Die Schweizergarde
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Seit 1506 schützt die Schweizergarde den Papst und seine Residenz. Verändert haben sich jedoch die Methoden und das Umfeld der Elitetruppe. In der traditionellen Renaissance-Uniform steckt heute ein junger, moderner und gut ausgebildeter Schweizer, der bereit ist, sein Leben für die Sicherheit des Papstes zu geben.

programme.title: Die Sonnenmenschen von Tokelau
programme.desc: Drei einsame Atolle mitten im Pazifik, die zu Pionieren in Sachen Energieerzeugung wurden: Tokelau ist die erste Nation der Welt, die ihre Stromproduktion zu 100 Prozent auf Solarenergie umgestellt hat.

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Indien, das Land der Spiritualität. Heiler und Gurus, sogenannte Babas, berufen sich auf höhere Mächte. Doch es gibt Widerstand gegen den gefährlichen Aberglauben und die Geschäftemacherei mit der oft verzweifelten Hoffnung auf Gesundheit. Rationalisten touren mit ihrem Science-Van im Dienst der Wissenschaft durch das Land und klären auf.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Der Kräutergarten von Java
programme.desc: Die hügelige Landschaft um Bogor ist der Garten Eden Indonesiens: Bekannt für seine artenreiche Vegetation und eine farbenprächtige Gärten. Hier praktizieren die Menschen eine Jahrtausende alte Pflanzenmedizin, genannt JAMU. Einst wurde das Wissen um die Wirkung der Kräuter nur innerhalb von bestimmten Heilerfamilien weitergegeben, doch heute ist es die Alltagsmedizin eines ganzen Volkes.

programme.title: China Moses, Joe Armon Jones & Luke Wynter
programme.sub-title: China Moses: 'Whatever' at Jazz à Ramatuelle
programme.desc: In 1988, Dee Dee Bridgewater was one of the first great jazz singers to perform at the Jazz Festival in Ramatuelle. In 2016, the story seems to repeat itself as her daughter China Moses took the stage at Ramatuelle. Over the years, China Moses has become a mature performer with a unique style: rocky voice, sharp sense of swing, and intense/energetic stage presence. After signing compilations dedicated to Dinah Washington and blues, Moses released in 2016 an album of his own compositions, entitled "Whatever". Get ready for a most entertaining performance combining jazz, soul, and hip-hop.

programme.title: Charles Bradley, William Aukstik, Frederick Deboe & Michael Deller
programme.sub-title: Charles Bradley: The Screaming Eagle Of Soul
programme.desc: This concert of soul singer Charles Bradley (1948-2017) was recorded in an intimate setting in Paris in September 2014. Before considering a career in music, Bradley had long tried to make ends meet with a series of small jobs. It was only in 1996 that he finally followed in the footsteps of his idol and soul icon James Brown, with whom he shared an exceptional ability to bring audiences to ecstasy. Bradley has developed a unique sound that combines funk, soul, and R&B, but still tinged with Brown influences.

programme.title: Cannonball Adderley, Nat Adderley, Yusuf Lateef & Joe Zawinul
programme.desc: Cannonball Adderley: Live in '63 boasts two beautifully filmed concerts from one of the most celebrated sextets in jazz history, captured at the top of their game. Cannonball Adderley (alto sax), Nat Adderley (cornet), and the masterful Yusef Lateef (tenor sax, flute, oboe), provide a massive three-horn frontline attack, while the stellar rhythm section featuring a pre-Weather Report Joe Zawinul (piano), Sam Jones (bass), and Louis Hayes (drums) fuel the songs with a deep infectious swing. Quincy Jones' "Jessica's Day" leaps from the gate with a huge big band sound that is extraordinary for only six musicians. This recording is a reminder that Cannonball Adderley was one of the most outstanding and highly respected alto saxophonists in the history of jazz. He was a bluesy jazzman who could play anything in superb fashion.

programme.title: Al Di Meola, Chris Carrington & Arto Tuncboyaciyan
programme.desc: 'Münchner Klaviersommer' was an annual concerts series that took place from 1981 to 1998 in Munich, Germany. Although the festival's name suggests a strong focus on piano music, it featured countless famous musicians from jazz and classical music – not just pianists. The concerts were usually held in July at The Gasteig, home of the Munich Philharmonic. In 1993, American guitarist Al Di Meola was one of the artists appearing here. With second guitarist Chris Carrington and percussionist Arto Tunçboyacıyan, Meola performs the now-classic world-fusion repertoire from his album 'World Sinfonia', which was originally released in 1991.

programme.title: Charles Mingus, Jaki Byard, Dannie Richmond & Johnny Coles
programme.sub-title: Charles Mingus And Eric Dolphy live in Liège
programme.desc: Charles Mingus showcases an exceptional concert performed in April 1965 featuring his most celebrated lineup: Jaki Byard (piano), Dannie Richmond (drums), Johnny Coles (trumpet), Clifford Jordan (tenor sax) and the great Eric Dolphy (alto sax, flute and bass clarinet). Recorded within an eight-day span, less than three months before Dolphy's death, the three concerts showcase Mingus's visionary leadership and the band's incredible depth and diversity with unique performances and arrangements of classics including ‘So Long Eric' and the groundbreaking ‘Meditations On Integration'.

programme.title: Jos van Immerseel, Anima Eterna Brugge, Claron McFadden & Bart Van Caenegem
programme.desc: Belgian conductor Jos van Immerseel leads Anima Eterna Brugge in a concert program dedicated to American composer George Gershwin. The program opens with Gershwin's symphonic suite Catfish Row (arr. Steven D. Bowen) which is based upon music from his famous opera Porgy and Bess (1935). This is followed by the well-known tone poem An American in Paris (1928). After, soprano Claron McFadden joins the orchestra, presenting a selection of Gershwin's classic jazz songs, including ‘The man I love' (1924-27), ‘I got rhythm' (1930), and ‘By Strauss' (1936). She also performs ‘My man's gone now' and ‘Summertime' from Porgy and Bess. The concert ends with Gershwin's celebrated Rhapsody in Blue, with Bart Van Caenegem as featured pianist. This performance was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on March 3, 2017.

programme.title: Vasilii Andreev
programme.desc: The award-winning Imperial Ice Stars are 26 Olympic, World, European and National Championship skaters, who jointly hold over 250 competition medals, performing theatrical ice dancing on a frozen theatre stage. The Imperial Ice Stars have received five-star praise from critics and standing ovations from audiences at some of the world's most prestigious venues - London's Royal Albert Hall and Sadler's Wells, Singapore's Esplanade Theatre, Montreal's Place des Arts and Cape Town's Artscape. This stunning performance, filmed at the Melbourne Theatre Company in Australia, offers a new look on the secular tale of Sleeping beauty, with the original music of Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky (1840-1893).

programme.title: Gustavo Dudamel
programme.sub-title: De Falla - El sombrero de tres picos - Suite No. 2
programme.desc: During the New Year's Gala 2010, the Berlin Philharmonic perform under the baton of Gustavo Dudamel, whose infectious energy and exceptional artistry have made him one of the most sought-after conductors by orchestras and opera companies around the world. They welcome mezzo-soprano Elīna Garanča, who has become one of the world's most famous singers within just a few years. On the program are various works by French composers, like Berlioz' Le Carnival Romain, Overture, Op. 9 and D'Amour l'ardente flamme' from La Damnation de Faust (Op. 24), Saint-Saëns' ‘Mon cœur s'ouvre à ta voix' and ‘Danse Bacchanale' from his opera Samson et Dalila and the ‘Habanera', ‘Seguidilla' and ‘Chanson Bohème' from Bizet's Carmen. The concert concludes with de Falla's Suite No. 2 from the ballet ‘El sombrero de tres picos'.

programme.title: Leonard Slatkin, Leonard Slatkin, Orchestre National de Lyon & Baiba Skride
programme.desc: Leonard Slatkin conducts the Orchestre national de Lyon in a concert recorded at the Auditorium de Lyon in France, 2013. The concert is a tribute to the organ of the Maurice-Ravel Auditorium, which was made by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll. The program features three works which premiered on exactly the same organ: Camille Saint-Saëns' Cyprès et Lauriers and Symphony No. 3 and Poulenc's Concerto for Organ, Timpani and Strings. Soloist is Vincent Warnier.

programme.title: Ballet of the Mariinsky Theatre
programme.desc: The Mariinsky Ballet performs 'Anna Karenina', a sweeping two-act ballet choreographed by Alexei Ratmansky. The ballet is based on Lev Tolstoy's 1877 novel that tells the tragic story of the married socialite Anna Karenina and her affair with cavalry officer Count Vronsky. The ballet opens where the novel ends: tormented by despair and loneliness, Anna throws herself under a train, whereupon Count Vronsky discovers his lover's lifeless body. Ratmansky's choreography is set to Rodion Shchedrin's music, which is performed by the Mariinsky Orchestra under the baton of Valery Gergiev. Among the dancers are Ulyana Lopatkina, Victor Baranov, Andrei Yermakov, and Svetlana Ivanova. This performance was recorded at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg, Russia, in March 2014.

programme.title: Lieder, Land & Leute zu Gast in Bad Waltersdorf

Diese Sendung steht ganz im Zeichen von heißen Quellen, romantischen Herbstlandschaften und hochkarätigen Stars. Mit dabei sind auch die Lokalmatadore aus der Steiermark, die Stoakogler. 1968 begann die Gruppe ihre musikalische Laufbahn und nach 43 Jahren Bühne haben sie 2011 ihre Karriere beendet. Sie präsentieren ein Medley ihrer erfolgreichsten Hits.

programme.title: Bei Hübner

Das besondere an ihnen ist, dass sie nicht nur an Land jagen, sondern auch im Ozean. Die Dokumentation begleitet Naturführer Cal Humchitt und sein Team auf den Spuren der Küstenwölfe.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Wir stehen alle auf irgendjemandes Speiseplan. Fressen, ähnlich wie Sex, bereitet allen Tieren Freude, wenngleich in geringerer Intensivität.

programme.title: Wilde Überlebenskünstler
programme.desc: Die Stille der Natur ist nur Fassade. Das Leben ist bestimmt von Anstrengungen und Kämpfen, großen und kleinen, die zu Sieg oder Niederlage führen. Diese Kämpfe betreffen alle und alles: Kämpfe um Essen, um Reviere und um Liebe.

programme.desc: Gober, die Orang-Utan Mutter, beherrscht den Film von der ersten bis zur letzten Minute. Über Jahre verfolgen wir die dramatischen Abschnitte ihres Lebens. Die Schicksalsschläge, die sie und ihre Kinder dabei treffen, berühren auch die Zuschauer.

programme.title: Sumatras letzte Tiger
programme.desc: Sumatra wurde von einer Welle grausamer Angriffe auf Menschen getroffen. Der vom Aussterben bedrohte Sumatra-Tiger sei Schuldige. Da sein Wald verschwindet, hat er keine andere Wahl, als das am häufigsten vorkommende Säugetier zu jagen.

programme.title: Anakonda – in der Welt der Würgeschlange
programme.desc: Yacu -Mama -die Mutter der Wasser Ein gigantisches Monster beherrscht die Flüsse des tropischen Südamerika: die bis zu neun Meter lange Anakonda.

programme.title: Penguins: The African Chaplin
programme.desc: Der Afrikanische Pinguin ist die einzige Pinguinart in Afrika. Wegen ihres unbeholfenen Auftretens werden sie als die Charlie Chaplins der Vogelwelt bezeichnet. Doch die bedrohte Art kämpft um ihr Überleben.

programme.title: Das Wüstenparadies
programme.desc: Die Sonora-Wüste im Südwesten der USA ist eine der artenreichsten Wüstenregionen der Erde. Zwischen bizarren Felsformationen und riesigen Kakteen entfaltet sich mehr Leben als in so mancher fruchtbaren Gegend.

programme.title: Tiere vor der Kamera: Die Nächte der Tasmanischen Teufel
programme.desc: Der Klassiker „Tiere vor der Kamera“ wurde von 1974 bis 2016 für den Bayerischen Rundfunk produziert. Die mehrfach preisgekrönte Serie von Ernst Arendt und Hans Schweiger lässt uns Tiere hautnah erleben – und mit ihnen lachen.

programme.title: Sardiniens wertvolle Muschelseide
programme.desc: Planet Wetlweit: Jedes Frühjahr findet auf Sardinien eine Prozession zu Ehren des Heiligen Antiochus statt. Die Einwohner legen Kostüme an, in den Kirchen werden Altartücher ausgelegt, die noch mit Muschelseide verziert sind - jenen Fasern, die die Fischer seit Jahrhunderten dem Meer entnahmen. Inzwischen sind diese Muscheln streng geschützt

programme.title: Cordóba, die Stadt der Patios
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Der ganze Stolz von Córdoba sind die Patios der Stadt - begrünte Innenhöfe, deren Wurzeln bis in die römische Antike und die Zeit der maurischen Herrschaft in Andalusien zurückreichen. Einmal im Jahr findet ein traditioneller Wettbewerb statt. Dann dreht sich alles um die Frage: Wer hat den schönsten Patio der ganzen Stadt?

programme.title: Kourou: Palmen, Raketen, Gefängnisinseln
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Lange war Französisch-Guayana an der Küste Südamerikas ein Schreckensort für Gefangene. Die Zuchthäuser dort galten als die härtesten Frankreichs. Heute sind von ihnen nur noch Ruinen übrig, die restauriert werden. Frankreich beginnt, dieses dunkle Kapitel seiner Geschichte aufzuarbeiten, nur einige Kilometer entfernt vom Weltraumbahnhof Kourou.

programme.title: Die Minenratten von Tansania
programme.desc: Im Forschungszentrum der Organisation APOPO in Tansania herrscht helle Aufregung: Eine Rattenmutter hat Junge geworfen - ein Riesenerfolg bei in Gefangenschaft lebenden Riesenhamsterratten. Schnell zeigt sich, dass einer der Rattenjungen besonders aufgeweckt ist. Er bekommt den Namen Ronaldinho. In nur wenigen Wochen lernt das intelligente Tier gefährliches TNT zu erschnüffeln.

programme.title: Montenegro
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Noch vor wenigen Jahren waren Esel in Montenegro vom Aussterben bedroht. Dass es die treuen Helfer noch immer gibt, ist vor allem Darko Savelji¿ zu verdanken. 2015 rettete der Biologe die erste, in elenden Verhältnissen gehaltene Eselstute. Kurze Zeit später nahm er zwei andere Esel zu sich, die als Futter für Jagdhunde geschlachtet werden sollten.

programme.title: Zuflucht in den Anden
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Am Tag arbeiten sie hart wie Männer. Am Abend verwandeln sie sich in das, als was sie sich fühlen: in Frauen. In ihren Gemeinden wurden sie verachtet und verstoßen. Auf den Kaffeeplantagen der kolumbianischen Anden, haben sie ein Refugium gefunden. Die Gemeinschaft von Transfrauen muss bis heute um ihre Anerkennung kämpfen

programme.title: Die Schweizergarde
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Seit 1506 schützt die Schweizergarde den Papst und seine Residenz. Verändert haben sich jedoch die Methoden und das Umfeld der Elitetruppe. In der traditionellen Renaissance-Uniform steckt heute ein junger, moderner und gut ausgebildeter Schweizer, der bereit ist, sein Leben für die Sicherheit des Papstes zu geben.

programme.title: Die Sonnenmenschen von Tokelau
programme.desc: Drei einsame Atolle mitten im Pazifik, die zu Pionieren in Sachen Energieerzeugung wurden: Tokelau ist die erste Nation der Welt, die ihre Stromproduktion zu 100 Prozent auf Solarenergie umgestellt hat.

programme.title: Indien
programme.desc: Planet Weltweit: Indien, das Land der Spiritualität. Heiler und Gurus, sogenannte Babas, berufen sich auf höhere Mächte. Doch es gibt Widerstand gegen den gefährlichen Aberglauben und die Geschäftemacherei mit der oft verzweifelten Hoffnung auf Gesundheit. Rationalisten touren mit ihrem Science-Van im Dienst der Wissenschaft durch das Land und klären auf.

programme.title: Just Cooking | Trailer
programme.desc: Just Cooking bringt Kochbegeisterten das einzigartige Paket an frischen neuen Food-Trends und junger Kreativität auf den TV. Aber auch Klassiker und traditionelle Küche, sowie kulinarische Dokumentationen und Reisevlogs werden gezeigt.

programme.title: Der Kräutergarten von Java
programme.desc: Die hügelige Landschaft um Bogor ist der Garten Eden Indonesiens: Bekannt für seine artenreiche Vegetation und eine farbenprächtige Gärten. Hier praktizieren die Menschen eine Jahrtausende alte Pflanzenmedizin, genannt JAMU. Einst wurde das Wissen um die Wirkung der Kräuter nur innerhalb von bestimmten Heilerfamilien weitergegeben, doch heute ist es die Alltagsmedizin eines ganzen Volkes.

programme.title: [오늘도 평화로운 갯벌] 바람에 흔들리는 갈대숲, 순천만
programme.desc: 순천만은 남해안 중서부에 위치한 만으로, 갯벌에 펼쳐지는 갈대밭과 칠면초 군락 등이 어우러져 아름다운 해안 생태경관을 보입니다. 넓은 갯벌에는 다양한 갯벌 생물들이 살고, 천연기념물인 흑두루미를 비롯한 국제 희귀 조류가 찾는 순천만의 풍경을 감상해 보세요! ※ 전라남도 순천시 순천만 (명승 제41호) / 한국의 갯벌 (2021년 유네스코 세계자연유산)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 대숲 소리를 부르는 손길. 채상장
programme.desc: 채상장은 채죽상자(彩竹箱子)의 줄임말로 얇게 저민 대나무 껍질을 알록달록 예쁘게 색색으로 물을 들여 다채로운 기하학적 무늬로 고리 등을 엮어 만드는 장인입니다. 채상장 보유자 서신정 장인의 염색한 대오리를 엮는 과정을 ASMR로 감상해보시죠. (서신정 / 국가무형문화재 채상장 보유자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 은은한 향기로움. 제다, 차 만들기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널이른 새벽 지리산 자락, 소나무 숲 사이로 할머니들이 토독토독 야생 찻잎을 땁니다. 화엄사의 작은 암자에서 스님은 할머니들이 따오신 찻잎을 덖을 준비를 서두릅니다. 차나무의 싹, 잎 어린줄기를 여러 공정을 거쳐 마실 수 있는 차(茶)로 만드는 전통기술인 제다의 과정을 영상으로 만나보세요. (덕제 스님 / 구례 화엄사 구층암 암주)

programme.title: 작품이 되기 위한 인고의 시간. 바닥파기
programme.desc: 벼루는 물을 붓고 먹을 가는 돌을 말합니다. 단양 자석벼루는 붉은색을 띄는 원석으로 만들어집니다. 자석벼루장인이 벼루를 만들어내기 위해 바닥을 파내는 과정을 영상으로 담았습니다. 장인의 집요하고 끈기있는 벼루 제작과정을 ASMR영상을 통하여 함께 만나보시죠. (신재민 / 충북무형문화재 자석벼루장 전승교육사)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 조선 도예의 맥을 잇다. 사기장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널백산 가문은 조선 영조시대 이래 300여년이 넘는 세월 동안 전통 도자기의 명맥을 이어오고 있습니다. 7대 김정옥 사기장은 아들이자 전수조교 김경식 그리고 손자이자 전수생인 김지훈과 함께 9대에 걸쳐 조선왕실 도예의 계보를 잇고 있는데요. 흙, 불, 그리고 사람이 빚어낸 그릇이 섭씨 1300도 장작 가마 속에서 견딘 후 일상으로 다가오는 과정을 감상해보세요. (김정옥 / 국가무형문화재 사기장 보유자)

programme.title: 소리에 녹아든 삶. 제주민요
programme.desc: 제주민요는 제주 사람들의 생활이 고달픈 노동과 맞닿아 있어 이를 이겨내고자 부르던 노동요가 많으며 서정적이면서도 구슬프고 한스러운 느낌이 강합니다. 맷돌을 돌리며 부르는 노래는 제주도만의 토속성을 가장 잘 담고 있는 제주민요로 꼽힙니다. 제주 특유의 향토적인 소리를 만나 봅시다. (강문희 / 국가무형문화재 제주민요 전수교육사)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 경복궁, 비에 젖다. 우중궁궐
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널비 오는 날의 경복궁으로 초대합니다. 궁궐의 잿빛 박석 위로 떨어지는 빗물들은 박석 이음매를 따라 유유히 하수구로 흘러들고, 경회루가 못에 비쳐 아른거리는 모습이 있는 궁궐의 풍경은 내리는 비를 맞으며 궁 안을 걷고 싶어지게 하죠. 차분한 빗소리가 어우러진 궁궐의 아름다움을 함께 느껴보세요. ※ 경복궁 (사적 제117호)

programme.title: 오감이 가득. 궁중병과 다과상
programme.desc: 오감이 가득한 다과상을 만들어봐요! 쑥이 들어간 경단 쑥구리단자, 밀가루 반죽을 꼬아서 예쁘게 모양을 낸 한과 매작과와 소나무 꽃가루를 이용해 만든 전통음료인 송화밀수까지. 이번에는 청각 뿐만이 아니라 시각, 후각, 미각, 촉각 까지 담아보았습니다. (박영미 / 국가무형문화재 조선왕조궁중음식 이수자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 전통을 지키는 인내. 옹기장
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널한국인의 집집마다 적게는 네다섯 개부터 많게는 수십 개씩 가지고 있던 옹기는 한국 도자기 역사상 가장 오랜 전통을 지니고 있으며 널리 쓰이던 생활용기입니다. 옹기장 보유자가 만들어 내는 옹기의 전 제작과정을 지켜보고, 전통을 꿋꿋이 지키며 빚어온 옹기에 쏟는 정성과 인내를 배워봅시다. (정윤석, 정영균 / 국가무형문화재 옹기장 보유자, 이수자)

programme.title: ‘안성맞춤'의 유래. 유기장
programme.desc: 유기장은 놋쇠로 각종 기물을 만드는 기술을 가진 장인을 말합니다. 이중에서 주물유기는 쇳물을 일정한 틀에 부어 원하는 기물을 만들어 내는 방법으로, 안성의 맞춤유기는 ‘안성맞춤'이라는 속담이 생겨날 정도로 유명하게 되었습니다. 안성맞춤 유기장의 세계로 여러분을 안내합니다. (김범룡 / 국가무형문화재 유기장 이수자)자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널

programme.title: 술이 익는 소리. 막걸리 빚기
programme.desc: 자료 제공 : 국가유산청, 국가유산진흥원, 국가유산채널막걸리의 어원은 체나 거름망으로 막 걸렀거나, 방금 바로 걸렀다는 뜻에서 유래하였습니다. 전통적인 방법으로 막걸리를 빚는 '막걸리 빚기'는 생활 문화이자 국가무형유산인데요. 전통의 기법을 고수하고 있는 전천 덕산 양조장에서 막걸리가 익어가는 소리와 전 과정을 영상미 있게 담아냈습니다. (이방희 / 2003년 등록문화재 진천 덕산 양조장 대표)

programme.title: China Moses, Joe Armon Jones & Luke Wynter
programme.sub-title: China Moses: 'Whatever' at Jazz à Ramatuelle
programme.desc: In 1988, Dee Dee Bridgewater was one of the first great jazz singers to perform at the Jazz Festival in Ramatuelle. In 2016, the story seems to repeat itself as her daughter China Moses took the stage at Ramatuelle. Over the years, China Moses has become a mature performer with a unique style: rocky voice, sharp sense of swing, and intense/energetic stage presence. After signing compilations dedicated to Dinah Washington and blues, Moses released in 2016 an album of his own compositions, entitled "Whatever". Get ready for a most entertaining performance combining jazz, soul, and hip-hop.

programme.title: Charles Bradley, William Aukstik, Frederick Deboe & Michael Deller
programme.sub-title: Charles Bradley: The Screaming Eagle Of Soul
programme.desc: This concert of soul singer Charles Bradley (1948-2017) was recorded in an intimate setting in Paris in September 2014. Before considering a career in music, Bradley had long tried to make ends meet with a series of small jobs. It was only in 1996 that he finally followed in the footsteps of his idol and soul icon James Brown, with whom he shared an exceptional ability to bring audiences to ecstasy. Bradley has developed a unique sound that combines funk, soul, and R&B, but still tinged with Brown influences.

programme.title: Cannonball Adderley, Nat Adderley, Yusuf Lateef & Joe Zawinul
programme.desc: Cannonball Adderley: Live in '63 boasts two beautifully filmed concerts from one of the most celebrated sextets in jazz history, captured at the top of their game. Cannonball Adderley (alto sax), Nat Adderley (cornet), and the masterful Yusef Lateef (tenor sax, flute, oboe), provide a massive three-horn frontline attack, while the stellar rhythm section featuring a pre-Weather Report Joe Zawinul (piano), Sam Jones (bass), and Louis Hayes (drums) fuel the songs with a deep infectious swing. Quincy Jones' "Jessica's Day" leaps from the gate with a huge big band sound that is extraordinary for only six musicians. This recording is a reminder that Cannonball Adderley was one of the most outstanding and highly respected alto saxophonists in the history of jazz. He was a bluesy jazzman who could play anything in superb fashion.

programme.title: Al Di Meola, Chris Carrington & Arto Tuncboyaciyan
programme.desc: 'Münchner Klaviersommer' was an annual concerts series that took place from 1981 to 1998 in Munich, Germany. Although the festival's name suggests a strong focus on piano music, it featured countless famous musicians from jazz and classical music – not just pianists. The concerts were usually held in July at The Gasteig, home of the Munich Philharmonic. In 1993, American guitarist Al Di Meola was one of the artists appearing here. With second guitarist Chris Carrington and percussionist Arto Tunçboyacıyan, Meola performs the now-classic world-fusion repertoire from his album 'World Sinfonia', which was originally released in 1991.

programme.title: Charles Mingus, Jaki Byard, Dannie Richmond & Johnny Coles
programme.sub-title: Charles Mingus And Eric Dolphy live in Liège
programme.desc: Charles Mingus showcases an exceptional concert performed in April 1965 featuring his most celebrated lineup: Jaki Byard (piano), Dannie Richmond (drums), Johnny Coles (trumpet), Clifford Jordan (tenor sax) and the great Eric Dolphy (alto sax, flute and bass clarinet). Recorded within an eight-day span, less than three months before Dolphy's death, the three concerts showcase Mingus's visionary leadership and the band's incredible depth and diversity with unique performances and arrangements of classics including ‘So Long Eric' and the groundbreaking ‘Meditations On Integration'.

programme.title: Jos van Immerseel, Anima Eterna Brugge, Claron McFadden & Bart Van Caenegem
programme.desc: Belgian conductor Jos van Immerseel leads Anima Eterna Brugge in a concert program dedicated to American composer George Gershwin. The program opens with Gershwin's symphonic suite Catfish Row (arr. Steven D. Bowen) which is based upon music from his famous opera Porgy and Bess (1935). This is followed by the well-known tone poem An American in Paris (1928). After, soprano Claron McFadden joins the orchestra, presenting a selection of Gershwin's classic jazz songs, including ‘The man I love' (1924-27), ‘I got rhythm' (1930), and ‘By Strauss' (1936). She also performs ‘My man's gone now' and ‘Summertime' from Porgy and Bess. The concert ends with Gershwin's celebrated Rhapsody in Blue, with Bart Van Caenegem as featured pianist. This performance was recorded at Concertgebouw Brugge, Belgium, on March 3, 2017.

programme.title: Vasilii Andreev
programme.desc: The award-winning Imperial Ice Stars are 26 Olympic, World, European and National Championship skaters, who jointly hold over 250 competition medals, performing theatrical ice dancing on a frozen theatre stage. The Imperial Ice Stars have received five-star praise from critics and standing ovations from audiences at some of the world's most prestigious venues - London's Royal Albert Hall and Sadler's Wells, Singapore's Esplanade Theatre, Montreal's Place des Arts and Cape Town's Artscape. This stunning performance, filmed at the Melbourne Theatre Company in Australia, offers a new look on the secular tale of Sleeping beauty, with the original music of Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky (1840-1893).

programme.title: Gustavo Dudamel
programme.sub-title: De Falla - El sombrero de tres picos - Suite No. 2
programme.desc: During the New Year's Gala 2010, the Berlin Philharmonic perform under the baton of Gustavo Dudamel, whose infectious energy and exceptional artistry have made him one of the most sought-after conductors by orchestras and opera companies around the world. They welcome mezzo-soprano Elīna Garanča, who has become one of the world's most famous singers within just a few years. On the program are various works by French composers, like Berlioz' Le Carnival Romain, Overture, Op. 9 and D'Amour l'ardente flamme' from La Damnation de Faust (Op. 24), Saint-Saëns' ‘Mon cœur s'ouvre à ta voix' and ‘Danse Bacchanale' from his opera Samson et Dalila and the ‘Habanera', ‘Seguidilla' and ‘Chanson Bohème' from Bizet's Carmen. The concert concludes with de Falla's Suite No. 2 from the ballet ‘El sombrero de tres picos'.

programme.title: Leonard Slatkin, Leonard Slatkin, Orchestre National de Lyon & Baiba Skride
programme.desc: Leonard Slatkin conducts the Orchestre national de Lyon in a concert recorded at the Auditorium de Lyon in France, 2013. The concert is a tribute to the organ of the Maurice-Ravel Auditorium, which was made by Aristide Cavaillé-Coll. The program features three works which premiered on exactly the same organ: Camille Saint-Saëns' Cyprès et Lauriers and Symphony No. 3 and Poulenc's Concerto for Organ, Timpani and Strings. Soloist is Vincent Warnier.

programme.title: Ballet of the Mariinsky Theatre
programme.desc: The Mariinsky Ballet performs 'Anna Karenina', a sweeping two-act ballet choreographed by Alexei Ratmansky. The ballet is based on Lev Tolstoy's 1877 novel that tells the tragic story of the married socialite Anna Karenina and her affair with cavalry officer Count Vronsky. The ballet opens where the novel ends: tormented by despair and loneliness, Anna throws herself under a train, whereupon Count Vronsky discovers his lover's lifeless body. Ratmansky's choreography is set to Rodion Shchedrin's music, which is performed by the Mariinsky Orchestra under the baton of Valery Gergiev. Among the dancers are Ulyana Lopatkina, Victor Baranov, Andrei Yermakov, and Svetlana Ivanova. This performance was recorded at the Mariinsky Theatre in St. Petersburg, Russia, in March 2014.
